# Project Rules

## Repo Structure

```
/
├── elsewhere/       # Next.js app, API route handlers, UI, scripts
├── supabase/        # Supabase migrations/schema snapshots
├── backend-plan.md  # backend/product implementation notes
└── frontend-plan.md # frontend/design implementation notes
```

## Application Boundaries

- Browser code lives under `elsewhere/app`, `elsewhere/components`, `elsewhere/hooks`, `elsewhere/store`, and browser-safe helpers in `elsewhere/lib`.
- Server-only code lives in route handlers and server-only helpers. Keep service-role Supabase usage out of client components.
- App API responses should use the shape `{ data, error }` where practical.
- Shared TypeScript types live in `elsewhere/types` or narrowly scoped `elsewhere/lib` modules.

## Environment Variables

- Never hardcode secrets or live project credentials.
- Keep real values in `.env.local` or deployment settings only.
- Document variable names in `elsewhere/.env.example`.
- Only variables intentionally needed in browser code should use `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.

## Git Hygiene

- Never commit `.env` files, Supabase CLI temp state, script outputs, `node_modules`, or generated build artifacts.
- Commit source, migrations, docs, and safe examples only.
